{"type":"system","subtype":"hook_response","hook_id":"23c0f0ba-4de2-43f5-8067-47ca6a2edb51","hook_name":"SessionStart:startup","hook_event":"SessionStart","output":"{\"hookSpecificOutput\":{\"hookEventName\":\"SessionStart\",\"additionalContext\":\"Active instincts:\\n- [project 95%] Project rule (AGENTS.md §5): never invent esoteric correspondences. Always derive from the canonical `CORRELATION_MAP` (Phase 1, source of truth from Doc 06 §2). Cycle 114: \\\"Por que HOUSES_36 é derivado, não hardcoded: AGENTS.md §5 proíbe inventar correspondências esotéricas. CORRELATION_MAP (Phase 1) já é a fonte canônica derivada de Doc 06 §2. Derivação garante: ajuste no correlation-map aparece na UI e na engine de IA simultaneamente.\\\" Reinforced in cycle 115 (engine reuses the same canonical source) and cycle 118 (consumers aligned to canonical data). How to apply: write a derivation function over CORRELATION_MAP; never write a literal `Record<TraditionA, TraditionB>` in feature code.\\n- [project 95%] After fixing a \\\"missing module\\\" or \\\"import/export cannot be used outside of module code\\\" error in a Next.js Turbopack dev overlay, the overlay may STILL show the old error for several minutes because HMR caches the failure. The overlay's error is NOT ground truth.\\n- [project 95%] Prisma 7 moved the datasource URL out of `schema.prisma` into `prisma.config.ts`. The `datasource` block in `schema.prisma` must contain ONLY `provider`. Use `defineConfig` + `env()` from `prisma/config` for the URL.\\n- [project 92%] Differential error messages between 'user not found' and 'wrong password' let attackers enumerate which emails are registered — a classic account-enumeration vulnerability that bypasses every other auth hardening. Cycle 116 made this an explicit design rule on POST /api/operator/auth/login: \\\"bcrypt.compare + sign JWT + set cookie + retorna Operator (sem passwordHash). Mensagem genérica em credenciais inválidas (anti-enumeração)\\\". The login handler must 