{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_function_5rc47lijtaiw_1","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Title: The CHANI App | CHANI\nURL: https://www.chani.com/app\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nThe #1 astrology app for manifestation, self-discovery, mindfulness, and healing.\n[...]\nDesigned to make astrology both accessible and useful, the CHANI app combines ancient astrological wisdom with meditation and mindfulness to help you foster your relationship with the sky and support your wellbeing. From personalized birth chart readings to real-time updates on how the current astrology is affecting you, it features everything you need to guide you on your life’s journey.\n[...]\nUnlock detailed information about your birth chart — aka the snapshot of the sky the moment you were born. By getting to know every luminary and planet in your chart, you’ll come face to face with your personal power and life’s potential.\n[...]\nAstrology is not therapy, but it is therapeutic. With the CHANI app, you can support your growth and healing through guided meditations, written and audio affirmations, and a live journal — complete with personalized reflection prompts.\n[...]\nWith daily sign-specific horoscopes, planetary horoscopes, readings for the current Moon phase and sign, daily featured meditations, and more, we’ll help you unpack the astrology of the day so that you can make the most of it.\n[...]\nYou'll get a new, personalized astrology reading from Chani Nicholas each week.\n[...]\nAll of our content is written and recorded by Chani Nicholas and our team of professional astrologers. Because we believe that astrology is about being witnessed in all our humanity — and that requires a human touch.\n[...]\n© Chani Nicholas Inc. 2026\n\n---\n\nTitle: How This Company Uses Astrology to Make Business Decisions\nURL: https://www.inc.com/gabrielle-bienasz/how-this-company-uses-astrology-to-make-business-decisions/91254002\nPublished: 2025-11-03T17:11:57.000Z\nAuthor: Gabrielle Bienasz\nHighlights:\nHow This Company Uses Astrology to Make Business Decisions\n\n2026 Inc. Best Workplaces Awards Extended Deadline Tomorrow, February 27! Apply now.\n\nInnovate\n\n# How This Company Uses Astrology to Make Business Decisions\n\nAstrology app Chani looks to the stars for advice on its own decisions, including product launches and hiring. Here’s how you can too.\n\nBY GABRIELLE BIENASZ@GBIENASZ\n\nNov 3, 2025\n\nSHARE\n\nLinkedInFacebookXBlueskyLink\n\nADD ON GOOGLE\n\nChani Nicholas. Photos: Courtesy Chani; Mikus and Mark Morgan via Wikimedia Commons\n\nListen to this Article More info\n\n0:00 / 0:00\n\nAstrology—an art, science, or complete pile of baloney, depending on how you feel—is a tradition that goes back some 5,000 years. Proponents believe that the position of the planets influence conditions on earth, and that there’s a right and wrong time for nearly every human activity—including business activities. So naturally, that’s the philosophy that guides nearly all business decisions—from hiring to product launches—at the Chani app.\n\nChani is an astrology app and media company with just over 2 million downloads and an undisclosed number of paid subscribers. Last year, Inc. estimated the company’s annual revenue to be around $14 million. Founded by longtime astrological content creator Chani Nicholas and her wife, former Morgan Stanley associate Sonya Passi, the platform provides users with birth chart analysis as well as insight on dealing with certain astrological events, such as the infamous Saturn Return and the dreaded Mercury Retrograde.\n\nSabra Mohamed, Chani’s director of growth and marketer extraordinaire, wasn’t much of a believer in astrology before working at the company. But when she joined in 2022, she figured, well—as a marketer, you have to be able to sell anything, right?\n\nNow, after a few years working at Chani, Mohamed is a believer.\n\n“A lot of entrepreneurs will say, ‘It’s hard work, and I was lucky, I was there at the right time,’” Mohamed says. “We’re hacking that.”\n\n## What is electional astrology?\n\nAstrology focuses on the idea that the planets’ orbit in relation to each other can provide information about a person, place, or thing, and influence events or conditions on Earth.\n\nHere’s one way to think of it: If you check the weather, and you see one day it’s going to be sunny, you wear sunscreen and open a lemonade stand. If the weather forecast is thunderstorms and clouds, you might not launch your lemonade stand that day.\n\nExpand to continue reading ↓\n\n---\n\nTitle: A Tour of the CHANI App – Chani Nicholas Incorporated\nURL: https://chaninicholas.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/articles/8711720295187-A-Tour-of-the-CHANI-App\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: February 24, 2026 18:48 \n                 Updated\nHighlights:\nThe CHANI app combines ancient astrological wisdom with mindfulness and meditation, and offers the most detailed birth chart explanations available. It also includes personalized horoscopes based on the movements of the planets, real-time updates on how the current astrology is affecting you, tailored astro offerings to help you work with the astrology of the moment, a library of meditations and affirmations for daily use, a live journal where you can set intentions and track your growth with each New and Full Moon, and so much more.Our app is rooted in traditional Western astrology, and we use the Whole Sign House System, which divides the 12 houses — or spheres of life — equally into each zodiac sign, starting with your rising sign. Because of this, we intentionally provide you with rising sign content, as it’s your rising sign that determines the areas of your life that the current astrology is impacting. Since the astrological houses are what give us insight into how the current astrology is showing up in your life, the rising sign becomes primary, with the Sun secondary and the Moon tertiary.Please note that because astrology changes minute to minute, the CHANI app has to pull in new information to display and refresh, which requires a consistent internet connection in order for the content to load. To get the best performance and experience, we recommend having WiFi or cellular data turned on on your mobile device and enabling automatic app updates. The CHANI app is available on both Android and iOS devices. You will also need to have iOS 14.4 or later installed on your device in order to run the CHANI app on your iOS device or Android 9 or later (Android 11 or higher is preferred) to run it on your Android device. Read on to learn about the Free and Premium content on the app.\n[...]\n- Your Daily Horoscope — Each day, you will receive a horoscope that’s specific to your rising sign.\n[...]\n- Today's Moon Forecast — Here, you will see an explanation of the current Moon phase and sign.\n[...]\n- Planetary Horoscopes — In this section, you can see where every planet and point is located, whether or not it’s retrograde, and how long it will be where it is. Scroll through each one for a rising sign horoscope on how its movements are impacting you.\n[...]\n- *Daily Rituals — Recorded by Chani to help you make the most of the day’s astrological energy\n[...]\nAdditionally, Premium subscribers can engage in daily reflections or find moments of healing through our library of guided meditations and affirmations. There’s something here for every need and mood, including grounding, abundance, grief, winning, and many more.\n\n---\n\nTitle: Free & Premium Content In the App – Chani Nicholas Incorporated\nURL: https://chaninicholas.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/articles/1500001732421-Free-Premium-Content-In-the-App\nPublished: 2026-02-24T00:00:00.000Z\nAuthor: 3 months ago \n                 Updated\nHighlights:\nFree & Premium Content In the App – Chani Nicholas Incorporated\n[...]\nCHANI App Features & Content\n[...]\nThe CHANI app is free to download on both iOS and Android and includes a whole slew of features, such as:\n[...]\n| CHANI App Features & Content | FREE |\n[...]\n|\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| Daily horoscopes that outline how the astrology of the day will impact you. | X | X |\n[...]\n| Daily readings for Moon phases and signs with guidance on how to create lunar magic. | X | X |\n[...]\n| Breakthrough course - a 28-day course led by Ch\n[...]\n. | X | X\n[...]\n| Weekly astro offerings — including journal prompts, rituals, altar suggestions, and guided meditations — to help you get the most out of the week’s astrology. | X |\n[...]\n| The Year Ahead, which includes your yearly horoscope; sign-specific astrology readings each quarter of the year; insights into the main themes of the year ; a list of the key astrological dates of the year; and rituals, journal prompts, altar suggestions, and guided meditations to help you work with the astrology as it unfolds. | X |\n[...]\nDaily ContentYour personalized daily horoscopes, daily readings for the Moon signs and phases, and daily featured meditations allow you to unpack the astrology of the day and work with the current energy.\n[...]\nPlanetary HoroscopesHere, you\n[...]\nThe Astrology of the Week Ahead PodcastIn this weekly podcast, Chani\n[...]\nof the astrological events of the coming week\n[...]\nan in-\n[...]\nthe planetary movements\n[...]\n## If you activate a free premium trial, you can also enjoy and explore all of our premium features. Your premium subscription unlocks the following app content:\n[...]\nYour Birth Chart ReadingUnlock detailed information about your unique birth chart and get to know every luminary and planet in your chart, including how they interact with each other. We regularly add new content here so that you can learn about other facets of your chart, such as nodes, asteroids, and points.\n[...]\ngrow, stretch, and show\n[...]\nWeekly Astro Offerings These resources include a personalized astrology reading for Your Sign; weekly rituals, altar suggestions, and journal prompts; and a tailored guided meditation. They’re designed to help you work with the current astrology, set intentions, reflect, create magic, and heal.\n[...]\nPractice mindfulness, engage in\n[...]\nour guided meditations, affirmations, and sleep stories.\n[...]\nThe Year AheadThis section of the app contains key astrological dates for the year, your yearly horoscope, quarterly sign-specific astrology readings, and rituals, journal prompts, altar suggestions, and guided meditations to help you work with the main themes of the year.\n\n---\n\nTitle: About CHANI | CHANI\nURL: https://www.chani.com/about/about-chani\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\n#### Our mission is to make astrology accessible to everyone\n[...]\nWhen you know your birth chart, you know your personal power and life’s potential. You come face to face with your best self and your growth edges. And through it, you gain a clearer understanding of who you are, where you've been, and where you're headed.Being witnessed in this way not only clarifies our complexities and desires; it helps us better understand and prepare for the challenges we face. Astrology is not therapy, but it is therapeutic. It’s a relentless reminder that we are the way that we are on purpose.Our aim is to give folks the astrological tools they need to feel seen, feel safe, and heal. Because when you have the right resources, it’s a whole lot easier to unlock your calling and be of service to the world.\n[...]\n# Built by astrologers, invested in survivors\n[...]\nAll of our content is written and recorded by Chani Nicholas and our team of professional astrologers. We also partner with FreeFrom, which means we donate 5% of all company revenue and 100% of the proceeds from all CHANI x Gifted by FreeFrom products directly to queer, trans, Black, Indigenous, people of color, and/or disabled survivors of gender-based violence via freefrom.org. To date, we’ve generated over $2.5 million for survivors.\n[...]\n## our founders\n[...]\nChani Nicholas is a New York Times best-selling author and astrologer with a community of over one million monthly readers. She has been a counseling astrologer for more than 20 years, guiding people to discover and live out their life’s purpose through understanding their birth chart. She has been featured in the New York Times, the Los Angeles Times, Rolling Stone, the New Yorker, the Atlantic, and multiple Netflix series. And yes, she is our namesake.\n[...]\nSonya Passi is an entrepreneur, an anti-violence advocate, and the reason the CHANI app became profitable on day one of its launch. Under her leadership, the company has transformed from a simple blog to a media hub for self-discovery, mindfulness, and healing with over 3.5 million readers. She’s also set the standard for what it means to be human-centered in the tech world, leading the company in a zero-AI policy and establishing industry-defining employee initiatives focused on economic justice.\n[...]\npersonalized guide through life\n[...]\ns ups and downs\n[...]\nThe Chani App Chani’s Book\n[...]\nAstrology for radical self-acceptance\n\n---\n\nTitle: ‎CHANI: Your Astrology Guide App - App Store\nURL: https://apps.apple.com/us/app/chani-your-astrology-guide/id1532791252\nPublished: 2020-12-17T00:00:00.000Z\nAuthor: Stephanie.Craig\nHighlights:\nto the following FREE FEATURES AND CONTENT: - DAILY HOROSCOPES: Daily horoscopes to know how the astrology of the day will impact you. - MOON PHASES: Daily updates on the Moon’s phase and sign, and guidance on how to create Moon magic. - THE WEEK AHEAD: A weekly podcast that gives you a rundown of the astrology of the week and tips on how to work with it. - THE CURRENT SKY: A snapshot of what sign each planet is currently in, along with dates and information on when each planet stations retrograde. - ASTRO WEATHER: An astrological forecast of how the next 7 days will look on a collective level - BIRTH CHART: An overview of where each planet is positioned in your birth chart, and a summary of each planet’s role. We also offer PREMIUM SUBSCRIPTIONS that unlock all app content. This includes the following PREMIUM FEATURES: - BIRTH CHART READINGS & DESCRIPTIONS: Detailed insights into your unique birth chart. This feature unlocks every planet in your chart and the significant relationships they have with one another. - WEEKLY MAGIC & MANIFESTATION: Weekly readings, rituals, and audio offerings to help you get the most out of the week and its astrology. This also includes a personalized podcast for your rising sign, guided meditations and affirmations, journal prompts, and altar suggestions. With this content, you’ll get all of the tools you need to work with major astrological moments like New Moons, Full Moons, retrogrades, eclipses, and more. - DAILY FEATURED MEDITATION: A guided meditation for each day to help you make the most of the day’s astrological energy. - TRANSITS: A daily, hyper-personalized look at how the planets in the sky are interacting with your unique birth chart. These transits are time-sensitive and build upon your horoscopes by giving you precise insight into when and how certain planets will impact you. - YOUR YEAR AHEAD: A personalized astro-reading for the year that tells you what to expect each month, what the main themes of the year are, and how to work with the astrology via rituals, journal prompts, alar suggestions, and guided meditations. - A LIBRARY OF AFFIRMATIONS AND GUIDED MEDITATIONS: A library of audio meditations and affirmations to support you through all of your moods and needs. Who we are: CHANI is a queer, feminist-led team on a mission to support everyone in living their purpose. 5% of all our company’s revenue is disbursed directly to queer, trans, Black, Indigenous, POC, and/or disabled survivors of gender-based violence by freefrom.org. We believe in promoting economic justice from the inside out and that good business prioritizes personal well-being. That’s why no one on our team is paid less than $80K before benefits and each of our employees is offered\n\n---\n\nTitle: In Her Shoes: CHANI Is a Business Built to Last\nURL: https://www.thecut.com/article/in-her-shoes-podcast-with-chani-nicholas-and-sonya-passi.html\nPublished: 2024-12-13T19:11:50.000Z\nAuthor: the Cut\nHighlights:\nOn the In Her Shoes podcast, host Samhita Mukhopadhyay talks to founders about the most important decisions they’ve made for the health of their businesses — and for their employees and communities, too. This week, she’s joined by Chani Nicholas and Sonya Passi, co-founders of the astrology app CHANI. Partners in business and in life, Nicholas and Passi managed to turn CHANI into the second-largest astrology app on the market despite prioritizing sustainable, slow growth and never once taking VC money. The magic’s in their community-driven business model, which includes heaping benefits on employees and channeling money to FreeFrom, their nonprofit supporting survivors of gender-based violence. To hear more, listen and subscribe for free on Apple Podcasts or wherever you get your podcasts. You can also read highlights from the interview below.\n[...]\nSonya: When you join our team, we are invested in you from day one. Our intention is not work you to the bone, you leave, we replace you. We’re really wanting to hire people that will be with us on this journey and build that expertise and community internally that we are espousing externally. So what that means is we have to pace ourselves. And what Chani and I know as two people who have such extraordinary creative appetite that we could (to our detriment) keep working and keep creating is how important and necessary rest is to fuel our creativity. As we learned this for ourselves, as we learned what rest did for our own brains and our own capacities and our own health and our own balance, we wanted it for our staff. No company is more productive because they work a full 52 weeks a year versus a company that works 45. It’s just not true. I think the reason we are able to put out beautiful offerings is because we have built cycles of rest into our actual business model.\n[...]\nChani: It’s more than investing money somewhere. It’s more than giving money. It’s really about investing time and talent and in community mutual aid and sharing, right? If this election cycle and this incoming administration is going to teach us anything, it’s that we are our best thing. We are all we have. We are what we have. We are what we need to invest in. And we are what is going to keep us safe. Read any ancient tale about anything to do with greed and true abundance and happiness in life — it’s never gonna be the person who has everything that is the happiest. It’s gonna be the person who knows how to share things and knows how to be a neighbor and is willing to learn or to try to experiment. The world will make you terrified of being generous and terrified of sharing.\n\n---\n\nTitle: Developer Spotlight: CHANI - Discover - Apple Developer\nURL: https://developer.apple.com/news/?id=1q8czimj\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: Apple Inc.\nHighlights:\nIn the universe of astrology, Chani Nicholas is a shining star — she has a New York Times best-seller (You Were Born for This: Astrology for Radical Self-Acceptance), a massive and devoted podcast audience, and a huge social media following.\n[...]\nWith Chani, Nicholas says, she wanted to provide an experience only an app could, by “creating a personalized guide through life’s ups and downs.”\n[...]\nIf you’re accustomed to reading astrology in short blurbs, Chani will be a revelation: Extensive horoscopes and birth charts deliver insights based on your birth date and time, and the current position of every planet (and Pluto).\n[...]\nThere’s more to Chani than (really comprehensive) horoscopes. Guided meditations, journal prompts, and more are core to the experience.\n[...]\nEqually important to Nicholas are the app’s social justice initiatives: Chani was built by AnnieCannons, a queer-led development group whose engineers are predominantly survivors of human trafficking or gender-based violence. And 5 percent of the app’s revenue goes to survivors of gender-based violence through FreeFrom.org, an organization run by Nicholas’ wife, Sonya Passi, who also serves as CEO of Chani Nicholas Inc.\n[...]\nNicholas: I’ve taught workshops online for the past six years; they were really successful, but they were delivered in a fairly archaic way. Building an app seemed like the most organic thing to do next.\n[...]\nPassi: It was important for us to make this system of knowledge extremely accessible. We talk about the app being the blueprint of your life in the palm of your hand. But we don’t want to just give your horoscope in tidbits; we want to give you the tools to be in a constant dialogue with your own chart.\n[...]\nNicholas: Every single word is written by me and a team of astrologers who have years, if not decades, of experience. And the planets never stop moving! Whatever you write is gone by the end of the week.\n[...]\nThe app includes workshops designed to bring you into a closer relationship with your chart.\n[...]\nNicholas: What I note from people is how it’s become a ritual: listening to the podcast, doing the workshops, checking in. It’s evolving in a way where people are making it part of their self-care; there’s such community participation. On Sundays and Mondays, people post a lot of weekend pictures of themselves in the bath to social media. I hope their devices are OK!\n[...]\nbegan. It"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"071762b9-140f-4c64-af75-f70aaa42db96","uuid":"d2b69b00-d03f-4f09-a5ce-a7e61fd5c5bd","timestamp":"2026-06-10T18:52:08.261Z","tool_use_result":[{"type":"text","text":"Title: The CHANI App | CHANI\nURL: https://www.chani.com/app\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nThe #1 astrology app for manifestation, self-discovery, mindfulness, and healing.\n[...]\nDesigned to make astrology both accessible and useful, the CHANI app combines ancient astrological wisdom with meditation and mindfulness to help you foster your relationship with the sky and support your wellbeing. From personalized birth chart readings to real-time updates on how the current astrology is affecting you, it features everything you need to guide you on your life’s journey.\n[...]\nUnlock detailed information about your birth chart — aka the snapshot of the sky the moment you were born. By getting to know every luminary and planet in your chart, you’ll come face to face with your personal power and life’s potential.\n[...]\nAstrology is not therapy, but it is therapeutic. With the CHANI app, you can support your growth and healing through guided meditations, written and audio affirmations, and a live journal — complete with personalized reflection prompts.\n[...]\nWith daily sign-specific horoscopes, planetary horoscopes, readings for the current Moon phase and sign, daily featured meditations, and more, we’ll help you unpack the astrology of the day so that you can make the most of it.\n[...]\nYou'll get a new, personalized astrology reading from Chani Nicholas each week.\n[...]\nAll of our content is written and recorded by Chani Nicholas and our team of professional astrologers. Because we believe that astrology is about being witnessed in all our humanity — and that requires a human touch.\n[...]\n© Chani Nicholas Inc. 2026\n\n---\n\nTitle: How This Company Uses Astrology to Make Business Decisions\nURL: https://www.inc.com/gabrielle-bienasz/how-this-company-uses-astrology-to-make-business-decisions/91254002\nPublished: 2025-11-03T17:11:57.000Z\nAuthor: Gabrielle Bienasz\nHighlights:\nHow This Company Uses Astrology to Make Business Decisions\n\n2026 Inc. Best Workplaces Awards Extended Deadline Tomorrow, February 27! Apply now.\n\nInnovate\n\n# How This Company Uses Astrology to Make Business Decisions\n\nAstrology app Chani looks to the stars for advice on its own decisions, including product launches and hiring. Here’s how you can too.\n\nBY GABRIELLE BIENASZ@GBIENASZ\n\nNov 3, 2025\n\nSHARE\n\nLinkedInFacebookXBlueskyLink\n\nADD ON GOOGLE\n\nChani Nicholas. Photos: Courtesy Chani; Mikus and Mark Morgan via Wikimedia Commons\n\nListen to this Article More info\n\n0:00 / 0:00\n\nAstrology—an art, science, or complete pile of baloney, depending on how you feel—is a tradition that goes back some 5,000 years. Proponents believe that the position of the planets influence conditions on earth, and that there’s a right and wrong time for nearly every human activity—including business activities. So naturally, that’s the philosophy that guides nearly all business decisions—from hiring to product launches—at the Chani app.\n\nChani is an astrology app and media company with just over 2 million downloads and an undisclosed number of paid subscribers. Last year, Inc. estimated the company’s annual revenue to be around $14 million. Founded by longtime astrological content creator Chani Nicholas and her wife, former Morgan Stanley associate Sonya Passi, the platform provides users with birth chart analysis as well as insight on dealing with certain astrological events, such as the infamous Saturn Return and the dreaded Mercury Retrograde.\n\nSabra Mohamed, Chani’s director of growth and marketer extraordinaire, wasn’t much of a believer in astrology before working at the company. But when she joined in 2022, she figured, well—as a marketer, you have to be able to sell anything, right?\n\nNow, after a few years working at Chani, Mohamed is a believer.\n\n“A lot of entrepreneurs will say, ‘It’s hard work, and I was lucky, I was there at the right time,’” Mohamed says. “We’re hacking that.”\n\n## What is electional astrology?\n\nAstrology focuses on the idea that the planets’ orbit in relation to each other can provide information about a person, place, or thing, and influence events or conditions on Earth.\n\nHere’s one way to think of it: If you check the weather, and you see one day it’s going to be sunny, you wear sunscreen and open a lemonade stand. If the weather forecast is thunderstorms and clouds, you might not launch your lemonade stand that day.\n\nExpand to continue reading ↓\n\n---\n\nTitle: A Tour of the CHANI App – Chani Nicholas Incorporated\nURL: https://chaninicholas.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/articles/8711720295187-A-Tour-of-the-CHANI-App\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: February 24, 2026 18:48 \n                 Updated\nHighlights:\nThe CHANI app combines ancient astrological wisdom with mindfulness and meditation, and offers the most detailed birth chart explanations available. It also includes personalized horoscopes based on the movements of the planets, real-time updates on how the current astrology is affecting you, tailored astro offerings to help you work with the astrology of the moment, a library of meditations and affirmations for daily use, a live journal where you can set intentions and track your growth with each New and Full Moon, and so much more.Our app is rooted in traditional Western astrology, and we use the Whole Sign House System, which divides the 12 houses — or spheres of life — equally into each zodiac sign, starting with your rising sign. Because of this, we intentionally provide you with rising sign content, as it’s your rising sign that determines the areas of your life that the current astrology is impacting. Since the astrological houses are what give us insight into how the current astrology is showing up in your life, the rising sign becomes primary, with the Sun secondary and the Moon tertiary.Please note that because astrology changes minute to minute, the CHANI app has to pull in new information to display and refresh, which requires a consistent internet connection in order for the content to load. To get the best performance and experience, we recommend having WiFi or cellular data turned on on your mobile device and enabling automatic app updates. The CHANI app is available on both Android and iOS devices. You will also need to have iOS 14.4 or later installed on your device in order to run the CHANI app on your iOS device or Android 9 or later (Android 11 or higher is preferred) to run it on your Android device. Read on to learn about the Free and Premium content on the app.\n[...]\n- Your Daily Horoscope — Each day, you will receive a horoscope that’s specific to your rising sign.\n[...]\n- Today's Moon Forecast — Here, you will see an explanation of the current Moon phase and sign.\n[...]\n- Planetary Horoscopes — In this section, you can see where every planet and point is located, whether or not it’s retrograde, and how long it will be where it is. Scroll through each one for a rising sign horoscope on how its movements are impacting you.\n[...]\n- *Daily Rituals — Recorded by Chani to help you make the most of the day’s astrological energy\n[...]\nAdditionally, Premium subscribers can engage in daily reflections or find moments of healing through our library of guided meditations and affirmations. There’s something here for every need and mood, including grounding, abundance, grief, winning, and many more.\n\n---\n\nTitle: Free & Premium Content In the App – Chani Nicholas Incorporated\nURL: https://chaninicholas.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/articles/1500001732421-Free-Premium-Content-In-the-App\nPublished: 2026-02-24T00:00:00.000Z\nAuthor: 3 months ago \n                 Updated\nHighlights:\nFree & Premium Content In the App – Chani Nicholas Incorporated\n[...]\nCHANI App Features & Content\n[...]\nThe CHANI app is free to download on both iOS and Android and includes a whole slew of features, such as:\n[...]\n| CHANI App Features & Content | FREE |\n[...]\n|\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| Daily horoscopes that outline how the astrology of the day will impact you. | X | X |\n[...]\n| Daily readings for Moon phases and signs with guidance on how to create lunar magic. | X | X |\n[...]\n| Breakthrough course - a 28-day course led by Ch\n[...]\n. | X | X\n[...]\n| Weekly astro offerings — including journal prompts, rituals, altar suggestions, and guided meditations — to help you get the most out of the week’s astrology. | X |\n[...]\n| The Year Ahead, which includes your yearly horoscope; sign-specific astrology readings each quarter of the year; insights into the main themes of the year ; a list of the key astrological dates of the year; and rituals, journal prompts, altar suggestions, and guided meditations to help you work with the astrology as it unfolds. | X |\n[...]\nDaily ContentYour personalized daily horoscopes, daily readings for the Moon signs and phases, and daily featured meditations allow you to unpack the astrology of the day and work with the current energy.\n[...]\nPlanetary HoroscopesHere, you\n[...]\nThe Astrology of the Week Ahead PodcastIn this weekly podcast, Chani\n[...]\nof the astrological events of the coming week\n[...]\nan in-\n[...]\nthe planetary movements\n[...]\n## If you activate a free premium trial, you can also enjoy and explore all of our premium features. Your premium subscription unlocks the following app content:\n[...]\nYour Birth Chart ReadingUnlock detailed information about your unique birth chart and get to know every luminary and planet in your chart, including how they interact with each other. We regularly add new content here so that you can learn about other facets of your chart, such as nodes, asteroids, and points.\n[...]\ngrow, stretch, and show\n[...]\nWeekly Astro Offerings These resources include a personalized astrology reading for Your Sign; weekly rituals, altar suggestions, and journal prompts; and a tailored guided meditation. They’re designed to help you work with the current astrology, set intentions, reflect, create magic, and heal.\n[...]\nPractice mindfulness, engage in\n[...]\nour guided meditations, affirmations, and sleep stories.\n[...]\nThe Year AheadThis section of the app contains key astrological dates for the year, your yearly horoscope, quarterly sign-specific astrology readings, and rituals, journal prompts, altar suggestions, and guided meditations to help you work with the main themes of the year.\n\n---\n\nTitle: About CHANI | CHANI\nURL: https://www.chani.com/about/about-chani\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\n#### Our mission is to make astrology accessible to everyone\n[...]\nWhen you know your birth chart, you know your personal power and life’s potential. You come face to face with your best self and your growth edges. And through it, you gain a clearer understanding of who you are, where you've been, and where you're headed.Being witnessed in this way not only clarifies our complexities and desires; it helps us better understand and prepare for the challenges we face. Astrology is not therapy, but it is therapeutic. It’s a relentless reminder that we are the way that we are on purpose.Our aim is to give folks the astrological tools they need to feel seen, feel safe, and heal. Because when you have the right resources, it’s a whole lot easier to unlock your calling and be of service to the world.\n[...]\n# Built by astrologers, invested in survivors\n[...]\nAll of our content is written and recorded by Chani Nicholas and our team of professional astrologers. We also partner with FreeFrom, which means we donate 5% of all company revenue and 100% of the proceeds from all CHANI x Gifted by FreeFrom products directly to queer, trans, Black, Indigenous, people of color, and/or disabled survivors of gender-based violence via freefrom.org. To date, we’ve generated over $2.5 million for survivors.\n[...]\n## our founders\n[...]\nChani Nicholas is a New York Times best-selling author and astrologer with a community of over one million monthly readers. She has been a counseling astrologer for more than 20 years, guiding people to discover and live out their life’s purpose through understanding their birth chart. She has been featured in the New York Times, the Los Angeles Times, Rolling Stone, the New Yorker, the Atlantic, and multiple Netflix series. And yes, she is our namesake.\n[...]\nSonya Passi is an entrepreneur, an anti-violence advocate, and the reason the CHANI app became profitable on day one of its launch. Under her leadership, the company has transformed from a simple blog to a media hub for self-discovery, mindfulness, and healing with over 3.5 million readers. She’s also set the standard for what it means to be human-centered in the tech world, leading the company in a zero-AI policy and establishing industry-defining employee initiatives focused on economic justice.\n[...]\npersonalized guide through life\n[...]\ns ups and downs\n[...]\nThe Chani App Chani’s Book\n[...]\nAstrology for radical self-acceptance\n\n---\n\nTitle: ‎CHANI: Your Astrology Guide App - App Store\nURL: https://apps.apple.com/us/app/chani-your-astrology-guide/id1532791252\nPublished: 2020-12-17T00:00:00.000Z\nAuthor: Stephanie.Craig\nHighlights:\nto the following FREE FEATURES AND CONTENT: - DAILY HOROSCOPES: Daily horoscopes to know how the astrology of the day will impact you. - MOON PHASES: Daily updates on the Moon’s phase and sign, and guidance on how to create Moon magic. - THE WEEK AHEAD: A weekly podcast that gives you a rundown of the astrology of the week and tips on how to work with it. - THE CURRENT SKY: A snapshot of what sign each planet is currently in, along with dates and information on when each planet stations retrograde. - ASTRO WEATHER: An astrological forecast of how the next 7 days will look on a collective level - BIRTH CHART: An overview of where each planet is positioned in your birth chart, and a summary of each planet’s role. We also offer PREMIUM SUBSCRIPTIONS that unlock all app content. This includes the following PREMIUM FEATURES: - BIRTH CHART READINGS & DESCRIPTIONS: Detailed insights into your unique birth chart. This feature unlocks every planet in your chart and the significant relationships they have with one another. - WEEKLY MAGIC & MANIFESTATION: Weekly readings, rituals, and audio offerings to help you get the most out of the week and its astrology. This also includes a personalized podcast for your rising sign, guided meditations and affirmations, journal prompts, and altar suggestions. With this content, you’ll get all of the tools you need to work with major astrological moments like New Moons, Full Moons, retrogrades, eclipses, and more. - DAILY FEATURED MEDITATION: A guided meditation for each day to help you make the most of the day’s astrological energy. - TRANSITS: A daily, hyper-personalized look at how the planets in the sky are interacting with your unique birth chart. These transits are time-sensitive and build upon your horoscopes by giving you precise insight into when and how certain planets will impact you. - YOUR YEAR AHEAD: A personalized astro-reading for the year that tells you what to expect each month, what the main themes of the year are, and how to work with the astrology via rituals, journal prompts, alar suggestions, and guided meditations. - A LIBRARY OF AFFIRMATIONS AND GUIDED MEDITATIONS: A library of audio meditations and affirmations to support you through all of your moods and needs. Who we are: CHANI is a queer, feminist-led team on a mission to support everyone in living their purpose. 5% of all our company’s revenue is disbursed directly to queer, trans, Black, Indigenous, POC, and/or disabled survivors of gender-based violence by freefrom.org. We believe in promoting economic justice from the inside out and that good business prioritizes personal well-being. That’s why no one on our team is paid less than $80K before benefits and each of our employees is offered\n\n---\n\nTitle: In Her Shoes: CHANI Is a Business Built to Last\nURL: https://www.thecut.com/article/in-her-shoes-podcast-with-chani-nicholas-and-sonya-passi.html\nPublished: 2024-12-13T19:11:50.000Z\nAuthor: the Cut\nHighlights:\nOn the In Her Shoes podcast, host Samhita Mukhopadhyay talks to founders about the most important decisions they’ve made for the health of their businesses — and for their employees and communities, too. This week, she’s joined by Chani Nicholas and Sonya Passi, co-founders of the astrology app CHANI. Partners in business and in life, Nicholas and Passi managed to turn CHANI into the second-largest astrology app on the market despite prioritizing sustainable, slow growth and never once taking VC money. The magic’s in their community-driven business model, which includes heaping benefits on employees and channeling money to FreeFrom, their nonprofit supporting survivors of gender-based violence. To hear more, listen and subscribe for free on Apple Podcasts or wherever you get your podcasts. You can also read highlights from the interview below.\n[...]\nSonya: When you join our team, we are invested in you from day one. Our intention is not work you to the bone, you leave, we replace you. We’re really wanting to hire people that will be with us on this journey and build that expertise and community internally that we are espousing externally. So what that means is we have to pace ourselves. And what Chani and I know as two people who have such extraordinary creative appetite that we could (to our detriment) keep working and keep creating is how important and necessary rest is to fuel our creativity. As we learned this for ourselves, as we learned what rest did for our own brains and our own capacities and our own health and our own balance, we wanted it for our staff. No company is more productive because they work a full 52 weeks a year versus a company that works 45. It’s just not true. I think the reason we are able to put out beautiful offerings is because we have built cycles of rest into our actual business model.\n[...]\nChani: It’s more than investing money somewhere. It’s more than giving money. It’s really about investing time and talent and in community mutual aid and sharing, right? If this election cycle and this incoming administration is going to teach us anything, it’s that we are our best thing. We are all we have. We are what we have. We are what we need to invest in. And we are what is going to keep us safe. Read any ancient tale about anything to do with greed and true abundance and happiness in life — it’s never gonna be the person who has everything that is the happiest. It’s gonna be the person who knows how to share things and knows how to be a neighbor and is willing to learn or to try to experiment. The world will make you terrified of being generous and terrified of sharing.\n\n---\n\nTitle: Developer Spotlight: CHANI - Discover - Apple Developer\nURL: https://developer.apple.com/news/?id=1q8czimj\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: Apple Inc.\nHighlights:\nIn the universe of astrology, Chani Nicholas is a shining star — she has a New York Times best-seller (You Were Born for This: Astrology for Radical Self-Acceptance), a massive and devoted podcast audience, and a huge social media following.\n[...]\nWith Chani, Nicholas says, she wanted to provide an experience only an app could, by “creating a personalized guide through life’s ups and downs.”\n[...]\nIf you’re accustomed to reading astrology in short blurbs, Chani will be a revelation: Extensive horoscopes and birth charts deliver insights based on your birth date and time, and the current position of every planet (and Pluto).\n[...]\nThere’s more to Chani than (really comprehensive) horoscopes. Guided meditations, journal prompts, and more are core to the experience.\n[...]\nEqually important to Nicholas are the app’s social justice initiatives: Chani was built by AnnieCannons, a queer-led development group whose engineers are predominantly survivors of human trafficking or gender-based violence. And 5 percent of the app’s revenue goes to survivors of gender-based violence through FreeFrom.org, an organization run by Nicholas’ wife, Sonya Passi, who also serves as CEO of Chani Nicholas Inc.\n[...]\nNicholas: I’ve taught workshops online for the past six years; they were really successful, but they were delivered in a fairly archaic way. Building an app seemed like the most organic thing to do next.\n[...]\nPassi: It was important for us to make this system of knowledge extremely accessible. We talk about the app being the blueprint of your life in the palm of your hand. But we don’t want to just give your horoscope in tidbits; we want to give you the tools to be in a constant dialogue with your own chart.\n[...]\nNicholas: Every single word is written by me and a team of astrologers who have years, if not decades, of experience. And the planets never stop moving! Whatever you write is gone by the end of the week.\n[...]\nThe app includes workshops designed to bring you into a closer relationship with your chart.\n[...]\nNicholas: What I note from people is how it’s become a ritual: listening to the podcast, doing the workshops, checking in. It’s evolving in a way where people are making it part of their self-care; there’s such community participation. On Sundays and Mondays, people post a lot of weekend pictures of themselves in the bath to social media. I hope their devices are OK!\n[...]\nbegan. It","_meta":{"searchTime":981.4}}]}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_function_5rc47lijtaiw_2","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Title: CHANI App Review - sun moresun\nURL: https://sunmoresun.substack.com/p/chani-app-review\nPublished: 2024-02-17T07:07:32.000Z\nAuthor: sun moresun\nHighlights:\n# CHANI App Review\n[...]\nFeb 17, 2024\n[...]\nIn a world increasingly seeking meaningful connections and self-discovery, the CHANI app emerges as a celestial beacon, combining ancient astrological wisdom with meditation and mindfulness. This review explores the app's features, user experiences, and the unique offerings that set CHANI apart.\n[...]\nUnlocking the Cosmos: CHANI promises to make astrology accessible and useful, and it delivers on this commitment by providing personalized birth chart readings and real-time updates on how current astrology influences your life. From the intricacies of your birth chart to insightful meditations and mindfulness practices, the app offers a comprehensive toolkit to guide you on your journey of self-discovery and healing.\n[...]\nContent Quality and Positivity: Others highlight the app's positive impact, praising Chani's uplifting readings and relevant content. The organization of the natal chart by planet with associated \"gifts\" and \"challenges\" is lauded as revolutionary, providing users with a holistic view of their destiny.\n[...]\npoints to the app's potential for growth and enhancement based on\n[...]\nTransformational Experiences: Some users share profound experiences, describing the app as everything they've been looking for. The integration of journal prompts, meditations, rituals, and weekly readings creates a transformative journey, fostering a deep connection with astrology and oneself.\n[...]\nPositive Feedback on Premium Version: Premium users appreciate the thoughtful blend of traditional and modern astrology in the app. The clean UI, cohesive design, and a variety of features make CHANI stand out as a well-informed astrology app.\n[...]\nAccessibility and Inclusivity: Users commend CHANI for its inclusivity and support for the LGBTQ+ community. The app's commitment to economic justice, fair wages, and inclusivity within its team reflects in its values, resonating positively with users.\n[...]\nWhat Sets CHANI Apart: CHANI distinguishes itself not only through its rich astrological content but also through its commitment to social impact. Partnering with FreeFrom, the app donates a portion of its revenue to support survivors of gender-based violence, aligning its values with inclusivity and justice.\n[...]\nConclusion: The CHANI app offers a celestial journey that goes beyond traditional astrology. While some users express concerns about the subscription model, the overall sentiment leans toward appreciation for the transformative experiences and positive impact on self-discovery. With its unique features, commitment to inclusivity, and support for survivors, CHANI stands as a promising tool for those seeking radical self-acceptance through the cosmic lens of astrology.\n\n---\n\nTitle: CHANI App Review: Astrology Without Hype - Mavenhood Society\nURL: https://mavenhoodsociety.com/chani_app_review_astrology_without_hype/\nPublished: 2026-01-06T17:40:00.000Z\nAuthor: Nia Bonson\nHighlights:\nThe CHANI App is a popular astrology app that offers daily readings and in-depth information on signs, transits, and current astrological shifts. Chani Nicholas, the person behind it, has been on the astrology scene for more than twenty years, steadily building a following through writing, social media posts, and a YouTube channel. Nicholas also recently discussed her less mysticism, more emotional literacy, timing, and self-awareness approach to astrology in an in-depth interview on “ On Purpose with Jay Shetty”. Her approach, encouraging the use of astrology as a guide, carries through to the CHANI App.\n[...]\nThe app experience centers on carefully translating astrology terminology into clear, relatable, bite-sized pieces. Astrological conditions are introduced as influences rather than predictions, and when high emotions are likely in play, they’re named without drama.\n[...]\nNicholas relies on rising signs as the primary element of individualized readings. Daily horoscopes reference your birth chart, and the focus stays on internal movement, emotional currents, and recurring themes. Reading a daily entry feels complete in itself, and also fits within a weekly roundup. The app works equally as well when engagement ebbs and flows.\n[...]\nThe birth chart section is where the app offers its greatest depth. Planetary placements, houses, and aspects are explained in a\n[...]\n, clear format. Interpretations avoid defining personality and instead acknowledge growth and change across a lifespan. The chart serves as a reference point and encourages readers to return to it at different life stages to read it differently.\n[...]\nAudio content supplements the written material and feels like a friend is explaining the movie you just watched together. Guided reflections and short grounding practices are designed as pauses, and are delivered at a calm, unhurried pace. Similarly, rituals and journal prompts are presented as invitations rather than assignments. There is no tracking or progress indicator, and no performative element to completing any of it.\n[...]\nOf course, this app will not suit everyone. People seeking predictions or clear, set-in-stone answers may find the experience too understated or not gamified enough. The CHANI App has a coherent voice, design, and structure that reinforce the same message. The value becomes clearer with regular use, though occasional check-ins still feel worthwhile.\n[...]\nFor those already familiar with Chani Nicholas’ work, the app provides a focused and well-organized home for what they value in her writing. For new users drawn to astrology as a reflective practice rather than a predictive one, it offers a thoughtful and consistent entry point. My subscription is on auto-renew.\n\n---\n\nTitle: CHANI App Review 2026: An Astrologer's Honest Opinion | Aurae\nURL: https://www.auraeastrology.com/blog/chani-app-review-2026-an-astrologers-honest-opinion\nPublished: 2026-04-05T16:45:06.000Z\nAuthor: Aurae\nHighlights:\nThe CHANI app is a Western astrology and wellness application created by acclaimed astrologer and author Chani Nicholas. It offers birth chart readings, weekly horoscopes, new and full moon rituals, transit deep-dives, audio meditations, and workshop content — all written and recorded by Nicholas and her team of human astrologers, with no AI-generated content.\n[...]\nyour Rising sign — all written by human astrologers\n[...]\ngenerated by AI.\n[...]\nContent is released on a weekly cycle tied to real astrological events. New moon and full moon cycles receive particular attention, with rituals, journal prompts, and reflective content released around each lunation. Transit deep-dives cover significant planetary movements — Saturn changing signs, eclipses, Venus retrograde — with the kind of detail and nuance that reflects genuine astrological expertise.\n[...]\nCHANI doesn't treat astrology as a predictive tool alone — it treats it as a framework for intentional living. The new and full moon rituals in particular have developed a devoted following. These aren't vague suggestions to \"set intentions\" — they're structured, specific practices grounded in the astrological significance of each lunation, designed to help users engage actively with the energy of each cycle rather than just receive information about it.\n[...]\nBecause every piece of content is human-written, CHANI produces significantly less volume than AI-powered competitors. The core content rhythm is weekly — a weekly horoscope, moon cycle content released around lunations, and occasional transit deep-dives for major astrological events. There is no AI available to generate on-demand readings, answer spontaneous questions, or produce fresh daily content for every day of the year.\n[...]\nIt's an excellent fit for intermediate astrology enthusiasts who have moved beyond Sun-sign horoscopes, understand\n[...]\nsignificance of their Rising sign, and want weekly content that rewards careful reading. The moon ritual and meditation features make it particularly strong for users who want a practice rather than just information.\n[...]\nThe CHANI app is one of the most carefully constructed and editorially distinguished astrology apps available. Chani Nicholas's writing is a genuine differentiator — the kind of quality that changes how you experience astrological content and raises your expectations for everything else you read. The whole-sign house system, the wellness integration, the moon rituals, and the principled commitment to human authorship all reflect a serious, sustained engagement with astrological practice.\n[...]\n? The CHANI\n[...]\nis a Western astrology and wellness\n\n---\n\nTitle: CHANI: Your Astrology Guide - Apps on Google Play\nURL: https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?hl=en_US&id=com.chani_nicholas_inc.chani\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nI ended up going for premium after trying out the free version and free trial...and I don't think I'll ever drop the subscription unless I have to for financial reasons. I love knowing that there's no AI being used. I love the week ahead readings. The breakthrough course is SO useful (I've done it twice). I switched to CHANI from CoStar, and I've deepened my understanding of astrology and have started to better understand the planetary cycles and placements in my chart.\n[...]\nI really want to love this app! Most of the better/relevant content is behind the subscription paywall. I just subscribed through June, so I will update my review towards the end of that. Chani's readings are cute and uplifting, though maybe a little too sweet - I like things a little less sugar coated. I enjoy the \"current sky\" and transits sections, they have seemed quite relevant so far. I'd love to see the ability to add additional profile(s) so I can check on my partner or family's charts!\n\n---\n\nTitle: ‎CHANI: Your Astrology Guide App - App Store\nURL: https://apps.apple.com/gb/app/chani-your-astrology-guide/id1532791252\nPublished: 2023-09-25T17:00:44.000Z\nAuthor: Neveragainrhxjwbxjs\nHighlights:\nFREE FEATURES AND CONTENT: - DAILY HOROSCOPES: Daily horoscopes to know how the astrology of the day will impact you. - MOON PHASES: Daily updates on the Moon’s phase and sign, and guidance on how to create Moon magic. - THE WEEK AHEAD: A weekly podcast that gives you a rundown of the astrology of the week and tips on how to work with it. - THE CURRENT SKY: A snapshot of what sign each planet is currently in, along with dates and information on when each planet stations retrograde. - ASTRO WEATHER: An astrological forecast of how the next 7 days will look on a collective level - BIRTH CHART: An overview of where each planet is positioned in your birth chart, and a summary of each planet’s role. We also offer PREMIUM SUBSCRIPTIONS that unlock all app content. This includes the following PREMIUM FEATURES: - BIRTH CHART READINGS & DESCRIPTIONS: Detailed insights into your unique birth chart. This feature unlocks every planet in your chart and the significant relationships they have with one another. - WEEKLY MAGIC & MANIFESTATION: Weekly readings, rituals, and audio offerings to help you get the most out of the week and its astrology. This also includes a personalized podcast for your rising sign, guided meditations and affirmations, journal prompts, and altar suggestions. With this content, you’ll get all of the tools you need to work with major astrological moments like New Moons, Full Moons, retrogrades, eclipses, and more. - DAILY FEATURED MEDITATION: A guided meditation for each day to help you make the most of the day’s astrological energy. - TRANSITS: A daily, hyper-personalized look at how the planets in the sky are interacting with your unique birth chart. These transits are time-sensitive and build upon your horoscopes by giving you precise insight into when and how certain planets will impact you. - YOUR YEAR AHEAD: A personalized astro-reading for the year that tells you what to expect each month, what the main themes of the year are, and how to work with the astrology via rituals, journal prompts, alar suggestions, and guided meditations. - A LIBRARY OF AFFIRMATIONS AND GUIDED MEDITATIONS: A library of audio meditations and affirmations to support you through all of your moods and needs. Who we are: CHANI is a queer, feminist-led team on a mission to support everyone in living their purpose. 5% of all our company’s revenue is disbursed directly to queer, trans, Black, Indigenous, POC, and/or disabled survivors of gender-based violence by freefrom.org. We believe in promoting economic justice from the inside out and that good business prioritizes personal well-being. That’s why no one on our team is paid less than $80K before benefits and each of our employees is offered fully covered\n\n---\n\nTitle: ‘Yearning to be connected to something bigger’: Chani Nicholas on why astrology is having a moment - The Globe and Mail\nURL: https://www.theglobeandmail.com/life/article-chani-nicholas-on-why-astrology-is-having-a-moment/\nPublished: 2025-12-23T13:00:00.000Z\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nMercury was retrograde. It was something Ms. Nicholas, a Canadian-born astrologer and one of the most well-known astrology experts in the world, had warned about on Instagram all of November (which was when we met). “It’s making everything just a little stickier, trickier,” she’d said. The moon and the planets were working against us; the world was ripe for mix-ups, and miscommunication.\n[...]\n“You don’t have to\n[...]\nAstrology is having a moment. Horoscopes have always had their believers (case in point: the most-read daily story on the Globe and Mail website is almost always the horoscopes). But in recent years, millennials and Gen Zs in particular have led a resurgence in interest. One 2024 survey, for instance, found that some 63 per cent of Gen Zs and Millennials rely on astrology for career guidance.\n[...]\nAround the world, astrology has become a multi-billion-dollar business. And the New York-based Ms. Nicholas is at the centre of it. She has, between her hugely popular CHANI app and podcast, some 3 million followers. Her book was an instant New York Times No. 1 best-seller.\n[...]\nAny trained astrologer can deliver a reading. But Ms. Nicholas’s specific brand brings together the personal with the political. Through her app and podcast, she delivers astrology readings through a uniquely queer, feminist, and politically progressive lens.\n[...]\nThrough Ms. Nicholas’s eyes, mercury retrograde might mean that yes, we all need to pay closer attention to the details – to dot our i’s and cross our t’s. But it might also help to explain large, global and political events too. Like the millions of Americans who were suddenly without food benefits because of the U.S. federal government shutdowns. Or the leaking of Jeffrey Epstein’s e-mails. On Instagram, her posts are as much about the moon and the stars as they are Donald Trump, or the war in Gaza, or the fight for reproductive freedoms.\n[...]\nShe started writing and e-mailing essays to her friends – horoscopes with a side of political activism. It was meant as a creative outlet. In her mind, activists weren’t interested in astrology, and the spiritual community wasn’t interested in politics.\n[...]\n“It’s really the queer community that was like, ‘We love astrology and we are super political,’” she said. It makes sense to her that her most ardent followers come from the most marginalized communities.\n[...]\n“I think that our institutions have failed us. I think that a lot of our religious and social institutions have put conditions on us that make us feel like we don’t belong,” she said."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"071762b9-140f-4c64-af75-f70aaa42db96","uuid":"1a384515-ead8-43f2-987f-45e08b6e446b","timestamp":"2026-06-10T18:52:09.131Z","tool_use_result":[{"type":"text","text":"Title: CHANI App Review - sun moresun\nURL: https://sunmoresun.substack.com/p/chani-app-review\nPublished: 2024-02-17T07:07:32.000Z\nAuthor: sun moresun\nHighlights:\n# CHANI App Review\n[...]\nFeb 17, 2024\n[...]\nIn a world increasingly seeking meaningful connections and self-discovery, the CHANI app emerges as a celestial beacon, combining ancient astrological wisdom with meditation and mindfulness. This review explores the app's features, user experiences, and the unique offerings that set CHANI apart.\n[...]\nUnlocking the Cosmos: CHANI promises to make astrology accessible and useful, and it delivers on this commitment by providing personalized birth chart readings and real-time updates on how current astrology influences your life. From the intricacies of your birth chart to insightful meditations and mindfulness practices, the app offers a comprehensive toolkit to guide you on your journey of self-discovery and healing.\n[...]\nContent Quality and Positivity: Others highlight the app's positive impact, praising Chani's uplifting readings and relevant content. The organization of the natal chart by planet with associated \"gifts\" and \"challenges\" is lauded as revolutionary, providing users with a holistic view of their destiny.\n[...]\npoints to the app's potential for growth and enhancement based on\n[...]\nTransformational Experiences: Some users share profound experiences, describing the app as everything they've been looking for. The integration of journal prompts, meditations, rituals, and weekly readings creates a transformative journey, fostering a deep connection with astrology and oneself.\n[...]\nPositive Feedback on Premium Version: Premium users appreciate the thoughtful blend of traditional and modern astrology in the app. The clean UI, cohesive design, and a variety of features make CHANI stand out as a well-informed astrology app.\n[...]\nAccessibility and Inclusivity: Users commend CHANI for its inclusivity and support for the LGBTQ+ community. The app's commitment to economic justice, fair wages, and inclusivity within its team reflects in its values, resonating positively with users.\n[...]\nWhat Sets CHANI Apart: CHANI distinguishes itself not only through its rich astrological content but also through its commitment to social impact. Partnering with FreeFrom, the app donates a portion of its revenue to support survivors of gender-based violence, aligning its values with inclusivity and justice.\n[...]\nConclusion: The CHANI app offers a celestial journey that goes beyond traditional astrology. While some users express concerns about the subscription model, the overall sentiment leans toward appreciation for the transformative experiences and positive impact on self-discovery. With its unique features, commitment to inclusivity, and support for survivors, CHANI stands as a promising tool for those seeking radical self-acceptance through the cosmic lens of astrology.\n\n---\n\nTitle: CHANI App Review: Astrology Without Hype - Mavenhood Society\nURL: https://mavenhoodsociety.com/chani_app_review_astrology_without_hype/\nPublished: 2026-01-06T17:40:00.000Z\nAuthor: Nia Bonson\nHighlights:\nThe CHANI App is a popular astrology app that offers daily readings and in-depth information on signs, transits, and current astrological shifts. Chani Nicholas, the person behind it, has been on the astrology scene for more than twenty years, steadily building a following through writing, social media posts, and a YouTube channel. Nicholas also recently discussed her less mysticism, more emotional literacy, timing, and self-awareness approach to astrology in an in-depth interview on “ On Purpose with Jay Shetty”. Her approach, encouraging the use of astrology as a guide, carries through to the CHANI App.\n[...]\nThe app experience centers on carefully translating astrology terminology into clear, relatable, bite-sized pieces. Astrological conditions are introduced as influences rather than predictions, and when high emotions are likely in play, they’re named without drama.\n[...]\nNicholas relies on rising signs as the primary element of individualized readings. Daily horoscopes reference your birth chart, and the focus stays on internal movement, emotional currents, and recurring themes. Reading a daily entry feels complete in itself, and also fits within a weekly roundup. The app works equally as well when engagement ebbs and flows.\n[...]\nThe birth chart section is where the app offers its greatest depth. Planetary placements, houses, and aspects are explained in a\n[...]\n, clear format. Interpretations avoid defining personality and instead acknowledge growth and change across a lifespan. The chart serves as a reference point and encourages readers to return to it at different life stages to read it differently.\n[...]\nAudio content supplements the written material and feels like a friend is explaining the movie you just watched together. Guided reflections and short grounding practices are designed as pauses, and are delivered at a calm, unhurried pace. Similarly, rituals and journal prompts are presented as invitations rather than assignments. There is no tracking or progress indicator, and no performative element to completing any of it.\n[...]\nOf course, this app will not suit everyone. People seeking predictions or clear, set-in-stone answers may find the experience too understated or not gamified enough. The CHANI App has a coherent voice, design, and structure that reinforce the same message. The value becomes clearer with regular use, though occasional check-ins still feel worthwhile.\n[...]\nFor those already familiar with Chani Nicholas’ work, the app provides a focused and well-organized home for what they value in her writing. For new users drawn to astrology as a reflective practice rather than a predictive one, it offers a thoughtful and consistent entry point. My subscription is on auto-renew.\n\n---\n\nTitle: CHANI App Review 2026: An Astrologer's Honest Opinion | Aurae\nURL: https://www.auraeastrology.com/blog/chani-app-review-2026-an-astrologers-honest-opinion\nPublished: 2026-04-05T16:45:06.000Z\nAuthor: Aurae\nHighlights:\nThe CHANI app is a Western astrology and wellness application created by acclaimed astrologer and author Chani Nicholas. It offers birth chart readings, weekly horoscopes, new and full moon rituals, transit deep-dives, audio meditations, and workshop content — all written and recorded by Nicholas and her team of human astrologers, with no AI-generated content.\n[...]\nyour Rising sign — all written by human astrologers\n[...]\ngenerated by AI.\n[...]\nContent is released on a weekly cycle tied to real astrological events. New moon and full moon cycles receive particular attention, with rituals, journal prompts, and reflective content released around each lunation. Transit deep-dives cover significant planetary movements — Saturn changing signs, eclipses, Venus retrograde — with the kind of detail and nuance that reflects genuine astrological expertise.\n[...]\nCHANI doesn't treat astrology as a predictive tool alone — it treats it as a framework for intentional living. The new and full moon rituals in particular have developed a devoted following. These aren't vague suggestions to \"set intentions\" — they're structured, specific practices grounded in the astrological significance of each lunation, designed to help users engage actively with the energy of each cycle rather than just receive information about it.\n[...]\nBecause every piece of content is human-written, CHANI produces significantly less volume than AI-powered competitors. The core content rhythm is weekly — a weekly horoscope, moon cycle content released around lunations, and occasional transit deep-dives for major astrological events. There is no AI available to generate on-demand readings, answer spontaneous questions, or produce fresh daily content for every day of the year.\n[...]\nIt's an excellent fit for intermediate astrology enthusiasts who have moved beyond Sun-sign horoscopes, understand\n[...]\nsignificance of their Rising sign, and want weekly content that rewards careful reading. The moon ritual and meditation features make it particularly strong for users who want a practice rather than just information.\n[...]\nThe CHANI app is one of the most carefully constructed and editorially distinguished astrology apps available. Chani Nicholas's writing is a genuine differentiator — the kind of quality that changes how you experience astrological content and raises your expectations for everything else you read. The whole-sign house system, the wellness integration, the moon rituals, and the principled commitment to human authorship all reflect a serious, sustained engagement with astrological practice.\n[...]\n? The CHANI\n[...]\nis a Western astrology and wellness\n\n---\n\nTitle: CHANI: Your Astrology Guide - Apps on Google Play\nURL: https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?hl=en_US&id=com.chani_nicholas_inc.chani\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nI ended up going for premium after trying out the free version and free trial...and I don't think I'll ever drop the subscription unless I have to for financial reasons. I love knowing that there's no AI being used. I love the week ahead readings. The breakthrough course is SO useful (I've done it twice). I switched to CHANI from CoStar, and I've deepened my understanding of astrology and have started to better understand the planetary cycles and placements in my chart.\n[...]\nI really want to love this app! Most of the better/relevant content is behind the subscription paywall. I just subscribed through June, so I will update my review towards the end of that. Chani's readings are cute and uplifting, though maybe a little too sweet - I like things a little less sugar coated. I enjoy the \"current sky\" and transits sections, they have seemed quite relevant so far. I'd love to see the ability to add additional profile(s) so I can check on my partner or family's charts!\n\n---\n\nTitle: ‎CHANI: Your Astrology Guide App - App Store\nURL: https://apps.apple.com/gb/app/chani-your-astrology-guide/id1532791252\nPublished: 2023-09-25T17:00:44.000Z\nAuthor: Neveragainrhxjwbxjs\nHighlights:\nFREE FEATURES AND CONTENT: - DAILY HOROSCOPES: Daily horoscopes to know how the astrology of the day will impact you. - MOON PHASES: Daily updates on the Moon’s phase and sign, and guidance on how to create Moon magic. - THE WEEK AHEAD: A weekly podcast that gives you a rundown of the astrology of the week and tips on how to work with it. - THE CURRENT SKY: A snapshot of what sign each planet is currently in, along with dates and information on when each planet stations retrograde. - ASTRO WEATHER: An astrological forecast of how the next 7 days will look on a collective level - BIRTH CHART: An overview of where each planet is positioned in your birth chart, and a summary of each planet’s role. We also offer PREMIUM SUBSCRIPTIONS that unlock all app content. This includes the following PREMIUM FEATURES: - BIRTH CHART READINGS & DESCRIPTIONS: Detailed insights into your unique birth chart. This feature unlocks every planet in your chart and the significant relationships they have with one another. - WEEKLY MAGIC & MANIFESTATION: Weekly readings, rituals, and audio offerings to help you get the most out of the week and its astrology. This also includes a personalized podcast for your rising sign, guided meditations and affirmations, journal prompts, and altar suggestions. With this content, you’ll get all of the tools you need to work with major astrological moments like New Moons, Full Moons, retrogrades, eclipses, and more. - DAILY FEATURED MEDITATION: A guided meditation for each day to help you make the most of the day’s astrological energy. - TRANSITS: A daily, hyper-personalized look at how the planets in the sky are interacting with your unique birth chart. These transits are time-sensitive and build upon your horoscopes by giving you precise insight into when and how certain planets will impact you. - YOUR YEAR AHEAD: A personalized astro-reading for the year that tells you what to expect each month, what the main themes of the year are, and how to work with the astrology via rituals, journal prompts, alar suggestions, and guided meditations. - A LIBRARY OF AFFIRMATIONS AND GUIDED MEDITATIONS: A library of audio meditations and affirmations to support you through all of your moods and needs. Who we are: CHANI is a queer, feminist-led team on a mission to support everyone in living their purpose. 5% of all our company’s revenue is disbursed directly to queer, trans, Black, Indigenous, POC, and/or disabled survivors of gender-based violence by freefrom.org. We believe in promoting economic justice from the inside out and that good business prioritizes personal well-being. That’s why no one on our team is paid less than $80K before benefits and each of our employees is offered fully covered\n\n---\n\nTitle: ‘Yearning to be connected to something bigger’: Chani Nicholas on why astrology is having a moment - The Globe and Mail\nURL: https://www.theglobeandmail.com/life/article-chani-nicholas-on-why-astrology-is-having-a-moment/\nPublished: 2025-12-23T13:00:00.000Z\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nMercury was retrograde. It was something Ms. Nicholas, a Canadian-born astrologer and one of the most well-known astrology experts in the world, had warned about on Instagram all of November (which was when we met). “It’s making everything just a little stickier, trickier,” she’d said. The moon and the planets were working against us; the world was ripe for mix-ups, and miscommunication.\n[...]\n“You don’t have to\n[...]\nAstrology is having a moment. Horoscopes have always had their believers (case in point: the most-read daily story on the Globe and Mail website is almost always the horoscopes). But in recent years, millennials and Gen Zs in particular have led a resurgence in interest. One 2024 survey, for instance, found that some 63 per cent of Gen Zs and Millennials rely on astrology for career guidance.\n[...]\nAround the world, astrology has become a multi-billion-dollar business. And the New York-based Ms. Nicholas is at the centre of it. She has, between her hugely popular CHANI app and podcast, some 3 million followers. Her book was an instant New York Times No. 1 best-seller.\n[...]\nAny trained astrologer can deliver a reading. But Ms. Nicholas’s specific brand brings together the personal with the political. Through her app and podcast, she delivers astrology readings through a uniquely queer, feminist, and politically progressive lens.\n[...]\nThrough Ms. Nicholas’s eyes, mercury retrograde might mean that yes, we all need to pay closer attention to the details – to dot our i’s and cross our t’s. But it might also help to explain large, global and political events too. Like the millions of Americans who were suddenly without food benefits because of the U.S. federal government shutdowns. Or the leaking of Jeffrey Epstein’s e-mails. On Instagram, her posts are as much about the moon and the stars as they are Donald Trump, or the war in Gaza, or the fight for reproductive freedoms.\n[...]\nShe started writing and e-mailing essays to her friends – horoscopes with a side of political activism. It was meant as a creative outlet. In her mind, activists weren’t interested in astrology, and the spiritual community wasn’t interested in politics.\n[...]\n“It’s really the queer community that was like, ‘We love astrology and we are super political,’” she said. It makes sense to her that her most ardent followers come from the most marginalized communities.\n[...]\n“I think that our institutions have failed us. I think that a lot of our religious and social institutions have put conditions on us that make us feel like we don’t belong,” she said.","_meta":{"searchTime":1151.8}}]}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_function_5rc47lijtaiw_3","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Title: What's your sign? - by Jacob Rushfinn - Retention.Blog\nURL: https://www.retention.blog/p/whats-your-sign\nPublished: 2025-07-31T14:34:43.000Z\nAuthor: Jacob Rushfinn\nHighlights:\nChani is doing almost $800k per month on iOS alone!\n[...]\nWhat’s even more interesting is that they only get 16-17k downloads per month.\n[...]\nThey have an estimated 1.2m lifetime downloads, and they’ve made $31M on those downloads!\n[...]\n#### They’re making $25-50 per download…\n[...]\nApparently, Chani Nicholas is an astrology influencer, so she is driving traffic to her app from her audience.\n[...]\nI’m guessing that the most engaged of the audience end up downloading the app, so they’re very high intent users.\n[...]\nBut then she talks about everything you get for free in the app. This would normally be advised against because it’ll make people less likely to pay…\n[...]\nWait. She doesn’t show a paywall?\n[...]\nDoesn’t everybody advise: “Make sure all new users see a paywall” ??\n[...]\nI had to tap around a little to even find a premium prompt.\n[...]\nThe paywall is decent, but have to scroll down to see the CTA buttons to purchase\n[...]\nNeither the annual or monthly are auto-selected, so I have to actively select a plan\n[...]\nI even went through with starting the trial because I was curious if she had upsells!\n[...]\nNope. No immediate upsells.\n[...]\nIf we do the math:\n[...]\n~16.5k new downloads last 30 days\n[...]\n~$800k revenue last 30 days\n[...]\n$48 per user\n[...]\nWith a $100 subscription, either:\n[...]\n40-50% of people convert to paying users\n[...]\nor she has crazy renewal rates\n[...]\nprobably a bit of both.\n[...]\n### I think it comes down to the fact that people love Chani (the person).\n[...]\nIt may not be\n[...]\nmore complicated than that.\n\n---\n\nTitle: How Can Chani Afford to Give Its Employees 7 Weeks of Paid Vacation?\nURL: https://www.inc.com/gabrielle-bienasz/how-can-chani-afford-to-give-its-employees-7-weeks-of-paid-vacation.html\nPublished: 2024-08-01T10:40:00.000Z\nAuthor: Gabrielle Bienasz\nHighlights:\n# How Can Chani Afford to Give Its Employees 7 Weeks of Paid Vacation?\nThe astrology platform has been profitable since launch in spite of–or perhaps because of–its generous benefits package.\n[...]\nRIELLE BIENASZ, EDITORIAL\n[...]\nISTANT, INC\n[...]\n“If the only way I can sustain this business is to pay people $11 an hour, I do not have a viable business model–because that isn’t enough money for those people to live on,” says Sonya Passi.\n \nThe co-founder and CEO of Chani,who is married to the astrology app’s eponymous co-founder and astrologer, Chani Nicholas, recently sat down with Inc. to discuss the merits of a more intentional and humanistic approach to business, why she chooses to build a sustainable culture for employees, and how to do it.\n[...]\nLos Angeles-based Chani, which incorporated as an S-corp in 2019 and launched an app in December 2020, offers myriad benefits to its 40-plus employees,includingday-one health insurance, unlimited paid time off, unlimited menstrual leave, about $10,000 annually in stipends, including a $1,500 use-it-or-lose-it vacation stipend, an $85,000 minimum salary, a four-day workweek, and seven weeks of mandatory, company-wide, paid time off.\n \nNone of those benefits have broken the bank.\n \nChani became profitable shortly after launching, grew subscribers about 50 percent year-over-year in its first three years, and has 250,000 active users on average, Passi says. She declined to disclose revenue, but for the sake of illustration, let’s say 40 percent of Chani’s average active users are monthly subscribers. If each of those 100,000 or so subscribers pays the platform’s $11.99-a-month subscription fee, then the company is taking in a little over $14 million a year.\n[...]\nThose numbers have attracted the attention of investors. Passi says she gets meeting requests from investors once a month, on average, which she ignores, and plans to continue ignoring, so that she and Nicholas can keep control of their company–and grow sustainably.\n \n“I’m not going to grow so rapidly that in two\n[...]\nNot every company\n[...]\nworking with the same\n[...]\nPassi is\n[...]\nemployers. She says, rest, benefits, and minimizing\n[...]\nthat’s difficult to calculate–and thatresearch has shown\n[...]\nworkers are more productive: “If the people working for you are able to bring their best talent and creativity and ideas to work, doesn’t logic tell you that your business will do better?”\n[...]\nsays.\n \nThat’s not to say every employee works out. Since 2020, Chani has “coached out” with support (in other words, fired) four people. The company currently employs 44 people. “For a small startup, that’s not a lot of turnover,” Torres says.\n\n---\n\nTitle: App Pricing – Chani Nicholas Incorporated\nURL: https://chaninicholas.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/articles/1500001732281-App-Pricing\nPublished: 2024-08-20T00:00:00.000Z\nAuthor: August 20, 2024 18:25 \n                 Updated\nHighlights:\nApp Pricing – Chani Nicholas Incorporated Skip to main content\n\nTrials can only be claimed once, so they are for new users only.\n\n| Premium Trial | Automatically Converts To | Cost (USD)* | Frequency of Payments |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| 14 days | Monthly Subscription | $11.99/month | Monthly |\n| 30 days | Annual Subscription (25% off monthly cost) | $107.99/year | Annually |\n\n- * Applicable taxes apply (depending on the state associated with your Google or Apple ID).\n\nTo activate your free trial, simply select the Transits tab or menu in the top right corner of the app (≡):\n\nIf you selected the Transits tab, you will be met with a paywall.\n\n- Choose the monthly or annual (best value) option, and proceed through the subscription process.\n\nIf you selected the menu, navigate to Account Settings;\n\n- Select the pink Subscribe button,\n- Choose the monthly or annual (best value) option, and proceed through the subscription process.\n\nYou can also choose to upgrade from a premium monthly subscription for $11.99 USD billed monthly, to an annual subscription, a 25% savings, billed yearly for $107.99 USD. With a paid premium subscription, you get access to a detailed birth chart reading, workshops for your week and year ahead, a library of meditations and affirmations, and much more. Learn about free and premium content in the app here. Information on our Cancellation and Refund policies can be found here. International pricing: exchange rates and taxes Apple and Google both convert the currency values of your purchase based on their own calculations, which may differ significantly from the exchange rate your bank is offering on any given day. As part of the automatic currency conversion, you may also be charged a digital services sales tax for the country associated with your Apple ID or Google Account.\n\n---\n\nTitle: How This Company Uses Astrology to Make Business Decisions\nURL: https://www.inc.com/gabrielle-bienasz/how-this-company-uses-astrology-to-make-business-decisions/91254002\nPublished: 2025-11-03T17:11:57.000Z\nAuthor: Gabrielle Bienasz\nHighlights:\nHow This Company Uses Astrology to Make Business Decisions\n\n2026 Inc. Best Workplaces Awards Extended Deadline Tomorrow, February 27! Apply now.\n\nInnovate\n\n# How This Company Uses Astrology to Make Business Decisions\n\nAstrology app Chani looks to the stars for advice on its own decisions, including product launches and hiring. Here’s how you can too.\n\nBY GABRIELLE BIENASZ@GBIENASZ\n\nNov 3, 2025\n\nSHARE\n\nLinkedInFacebookXBlueskyLink\n\nADD ON GOOGLE\n\nChani Nicholas. Photos: Courtesy Chani; Mikus and Mark Morgan via Wikimedia Commons\n\nListen to this Article More info\n\n0:00 / 0:00\n\nAstrology—an art, science, or complete pile of baloney, depending on how you feel—is a tradition that goes back some 5,000 years. Proponents believe that the position of the planets influence conditions on earth, and that there’s a right and wrong time for nearly every human activity—including business activities. So naturally, that’s the philosophy that guides nearly all business decisions—from hiring to product launches—at the Chani app.\n\nChani is an astrology app and media company with just over 2 million downloads and an undisclosed number of paid subscribers. Last year, Inc. estimated the company’s annual revenue to be around $14 million. Founded by longtime astrological content creator Chani Nicholas and her wife, former Morgan Stanley associate Sonya Passi, the platform provides users with birth chart analysis as well as insight on dealing with certain astrological events, such as the infamous Saturn Return and the dreaded Mercury Retrograde.\n\nSabra Mohamed, Chani’s director of growth and marketer extraordinaire, wasn’t much of a believer in astrology before working at the company. But when she joined in 2022, she figured, well—as a marketer, you have to be able to sell anything, right?\n\nNow, after a few years working at Chani, Mohamed is a believer.\n\n“A lot of entrepreneurs will say, ‘It’s hard work, and I was lucky, I was there at the right time,’” Mohamed says. “We’re hacking that.”\n\n## What is electional astrology?\n\nAstrology focuses on the idea that the planets’ orbit in relation to each other can provide information about a person, place, or thing, and influence events or conditions on Earth.\n\nHere’s one way to think of it: If you check the weather, and you see one day it’s going to be sunny, you wear sunscreen and open a lemonade stand. If the weather forecast is thunderstorms and clouds, you might not launch your lemonade stand that day.\n\nExpand to continue reading ↓\n\n---\n\nTitle: CHANI: Your Astrology Guide — Review 2026: Sentiment & Intel\nURL: https://marlvel.ai/intel-report/lifestyle/com-chaninicholas-chaniapp\nPublished: 2026-05-26T10:22:42.000Z\nAuthor: Marlvel.ai\nHighlights:\nFreemium\n- Signal: Rating 4.91\n[...]\nlate-night\n[...]\nHuman-centered\n[...]\nImplementation of a\n[...]\nto support comfortable\n[...]\nand early morning hours (top request)\n[...]\n| Fact | Value |\n| --- | --- |\n| Rating | 4.91/5 (58.3K reviews) |\n| User Mood | Thrilled |\n| Category | Lifestyle |\n| Developer | Chani Nicholas Incorporated |\n| Pricing | Freemium |\n| Platforms | iOS & Android |\n| Confidence | High (0.9/1.0) |\n| Data Age | 0d |\n[...]\nCHANI holds a #30 Grossing rank in the US Lifestyle category, maintaining a consistent top-50 presence across multiple international markets. The gap between its high user sentiment and the paywall-gated transit analysis suggests significant untapped revenue potential among existing free-tier users.\n[...]\n- Model: Freemium\n- Tiers: Free: Daily horoscopes, moon phases, birth chart overview, Premium: Full chart readings, transits, meditation library\n- Analysis: Freemium model uses high-value personalized transit data as the primary conversion gate for premium subscriptions.\n[...]\n- Latest (v2.1.0, 1 years ago): Free users gain unlimited access to “Abundance” meditations and previews for birth chart and transit insights. Added pull-to-refresh functionality for all users.\n[...]\nCHANI: Your Astrology Guide is a market-leading lifestyle app that is free with in-app purchases.\n[...]\nWith a 4.91/5 rating from 58.3K reviews, it delivers strong user satisfaction.\n[...]\n> Bottom Line: CHANI maintains a strong category lead through authentic, human-made content, but the lack of dark mode and high paywall friction threaten to erode the daily habit of its core user base, so the PM should prioritize UI hygiene to defend retention.\n[...]\n- [ ] [PIVOT] [MEDIUM IMPACT] Audit transit analysis paywall because low-income users flag it as a barrier → increase conversion rate — Sentiment data shows friction regarding the paywall for in-depth transit analysis. (trade-off: deprioritize Pause the meditation library expansion — optimizing current conversion funnels yields higher immediate ROI.)\n[...]\n| Metric | Value |\n| --- | --- |\n| Overall Rating | 4.91/5 |\n| Total Reviews | 58.3K |\n| Sentiment | Thrilled (92/100) |\n| Confidence | High |\n| Pricing Model | Freemium |\n| Platforms | iOS & Android |\n| Key Features | 3 analyzed |\n| Trend | Mixed |\n| Outlook | Stable |\n[...]\n### Is CHANI worth paying for if I am a beginner?\n[...]\nCHANI offers extensive free content including daily horoscopes and birth chart overviews. Premium features like detailed transits and meditation libraries are best suited for users who want to build a daily astrological ritual, but beginners can get significant value from the free tier.\n\n---\n\nTitle: CHANI: Your Astrology Guide UI Breakdown | ScreensDesign Showcase\nURL: https://screensdesign.com/showcase/chani-your-astrology-guide\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\n$450.0K/mo25.0K downloads4.9 rating9 onboarding steps\n[...]\n**App info**\n* **App name:** CHANI: Your Astrology Guide\n* **Onboarding steps:** 9\n* **Paywall type:** Free Trial - Soft Paywall\n* **Monthly installs:** 25,000\n* **Monthly revenue:** $500,000\n* **App category:** lifestyle\n[...]\n* **Freemium Teasers:** Courses offer the first lesson for free (03:29), giving a substantial preview of premium content and creating a value-driven reason to subscribe.\n[...]\nCHANI uses a freemium model with a soft paywall. Users can access a significant amount of content for free, including daily horoscopes and the first lesson of some courses. The paywall appears when a user attempts to access locked content, such as a premium course lesson (03:34). The paywall screen (03:35) presents two free trial options, an annual plan with a discount and a monthly plan. This strategy allows users to experience the app's value and build trust before being asked to pay."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"071762b9-140f-4c64-af75-f70aaa42db96","uuid":"1544c4b5-49a5-4f99-9245-849639751660","timestamp":"2026-06-10T18:52:09.274Z","tool_use_result":[{"type":"text","text":"Title: What's your sign? - by Jacob Rushfinn - Retention.Blog\nURL: https://www.retention.blog/p/whats-your-sign\nPublished: 2025-07-31T14:34:43.000Z\nAuthor: Jacob Rushfinn\nHighlights:\nChani is doing almost $800k per month on iOS alone!\n[...]\nWhat’s even more interesting is that they only get 16-17k downloads per month.\n[...]\nThey have an estimated 1.2m lifetime downloads, and they’ve made $31M on those downloads!\n[...]\n#### They’re making $25-50 per download…\n[...]\nApparently, Chani Nicholas is an astrology influencer, so she is driving traffic to her app from her audience.\n[...]\nI’m guessing that the most engaged of the audience end up downloading the app, so they’re very high intent users.\n[...]\nBut then she talks about everything you get for free in the app. This would normally be advised against because it’ll make people less likely to pay…\n[...]\nWait. She doesn’t show a paywall?\n[...]\nDoesn’t everybody advise: “Make sure all new users see a paywall” ??\n[...]\nI had to tap around a little to even find a premium prompt.\n[...]\nThe paywall is decent, but have to scroll down to see the CTA buttons to purchase\n[...]\nNeither the annual or monthly are auto-selected, so I have to actively select a plan\n[...]\nI even went through with starting the trial because I was curious if she had upsells!\n[...]\nNope. No immediate upsells.\n[...]\nIf we do the math:\n[...]\n~16.5k new downloads last 30 days\n[...]\n~$800k revenue last 30 days\n[...]\n$48 per user\n[...]\nWith a $100 subscription, either:\n[...]\n40-50% of people convert to paying users\n[...]\nor she has crazy renewal rates\n[...]\nprobably a bit of both.\n[...]\n### I think it comes down to the fact that people love Chani (the person).\n[...]\nIt may not be\n[...]\nmore complicated than that.\n\n---\n\nTitle: How Can Chani Afford to Give Its Employees 7 Weeks of Paid Vacation?\nURL: https://www.inc.com/gabrielle-bienasz/how-can-chani-afford-to-give-its-employees-7-weeks-of-paid-vacation.html\nPublished: 2024-08-01T10:40:00.000Z\nAuthor: Gabrielle Bienasz\nHighlights:\n# How Can Chani Afford to Give Its Employees 7 Weeks of Paid Vacation?\nThe astrology platform has been profitable since launch in spite of–or perhaps because of–its generous benefits package.\n[...]\nRIELLE BIENASZ, EDITORIAL\n[...]\nISTANT, INC\n[...]\n“If the only way I can sustain this business is to pay people $11 an hour, I do not have a viable business model–because that isn’t enough money for those people to live on,” says Sonya Passi.\n \nThe co-founder and CEO of Chani,who is married to the astrology app’s eponymous co-founder and astrologer, Chani Nicholas, recently sat down with Inc. to discuss the merits of a more intentional and humanistic approach to business, why she chooses to build a sustainable culture for employees, and how to do it.\n[...]\nLos Angeles-based Chani, which incorporated as an S-corp in 2019 and launched an app in December 2020, offers myriad benefits to its 40-plus employees,includingday-one health insurance, unlimited paid time off, unlimited menstrual leave, about $10,000 annually in stipends, including a $1,500 use-it-or-lose-it vacation stipend, an $85,000 minimum salary, a four-day workweek, and seven weeks of mandatory, company-wide, paid time off.\n \nNone of those benefits have broken the bank.\n \nChani became profitable shortly after launching, grew subscribers about 50 percent year-over-year in its first three years, and has 250,000 active users on average, Passi says. She declined to disclose revenue, but for the sake of illustration, let’s say 40 percent of Chani’s average active users are monthly subscribers. If each of those 100,000 or so subscribers pays the platform’s $11.99-a-month subscription fee, then the company is taking in a little over $14 million a year.\n[...]\nThose numbers have attracted the attention of investors. Passi says she gets meeting requests from investors once a month, on average, which she ignores, and plans to continue ignoring, so that she and Nicholas can keep control of their company–and grow sustainably.\n \n“I’m not going to grow so rapidly that in two\n[...]\nNot every company\n[...]\nworking with the same\n[...]\nPassi is\n[...]\nemployers. She says, rest, benefits, and minimizing\n[...]\nthat’s difficult to calculate–and thatresearch has shown\n[...]\nworkers are more productive: “If the people working for you are able to bring their best talent and creativity and ideas to work, doesn’t logic tell you that your business will do better?”\n[...]\nsays.\n \nThat’s not to say every employee works out. Since 2020, Chani has “coached out” with support (in other words, fired) four people. The company currently employs 44 people. “For a small startup, that’s not a lot of turnover,” Torres says.\n\n---\n\nTitle: App Pricing – Chani Nicholas Incorporated\nURL: https://chaninicholas.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/articles/1500001732281-App-Pricing\nPublished: 2024-08-20T00:00:00.000Z\nAuthor: August 20, 2024 18:25 \n                 Updated\nHighlights:\nApp Pricing – Chani Nicholas Incorporated Skip to main content\n\nTrials can only be claimed once, so they are for new users only.\n\n| Premium Trial | Automatically Converts To | Cost (USD)* | Frequency of Payments |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| 14 days | Monthly Subscription | $11.99/month | Monthly |\n| 30 days | Annual Subscription (25% off monthly cost) | $107.99/year | Annually |\n\n- * Applicable taxes apply (depending on the state associated with your Google or Apple ID).\n\nTo activate your free trial, simply select the Transits tab or menu in the top right corner of the app (≡):\n\nIf you selected the Transits tab, you will be met with a paywall.\n\n- Choose the monthly or annual (best value) option, and proceed through the subscription process.\n\nIf you selected the menu, navigate to Account Settings;\n\n- Select the pink Subscribe button,\n- Choose the monthly or annual (best value) option, and proceed through the subscription process.\n\nYou can also choose to upgrade from a premium monthly subscription for $11.99 USD billed monthly, to an annual subscription, a 25% savings, billed yearly for $107.99 USD. With a paid premium subscription, you get access to a detailed birth chart reading, workshops for your week and year ahead, a library of meditations and affirmations, and much more. Learn about free and premium content in the app here. Information on our Cancellation and Refund policies can be found here. International pricing: exchange rates and taxes Apple and Google both convert the currency values of your purchase based on their own calculations, which may differ significantly from the exchange rate your bank is offering on any given day. As part of the automatic currency conversion, you may also be charged a digital services sales tax for the country associated with your Apple ID or Google Account.\n\n---\n\nTitle: How This Company Uses Astrology to Make Business Decisions\nURL: https://www.inc.com/gabrielle-bienasz/how-this-company-uses-astrology-to-make-business-decisions/91254002\nPublished: 2025-11-03T17:11:57.000Z\nAuthor: Gabrielle Bienasz\nHighlights:\nHow This Company Uses Astrology to Make Business Decisions\n\n2026 Inc. Best Workplaces Awards Extended Deadline Tomorrow, February 27! Apply now.\n\nInnovate\n\n# How This Company Uses Astrology to Make Business Decisions\n\nAstrology app Chani looks to the stars for advice on its own decisions, including product launches and hiring. Here’s how you can too.\n\nBY GABRIELLE BIENASZ@GBIENASZ\n\nNov 3, 2025\n\nSHARE\n\nLinkedInFacebookXBlueskyLink\n\nADD ON GOOGLE\n\nChani Nicholas. Photos: Courtesy Chani; Mikus and Mark Morgan via Wikimedia Commons\n\nListen to this Article More info\n\n0:00 / 0:00\n\nAstrology—an art, science, or complete pile of baloney, depending on how you feel—is a tradition that goes back some 5,000 years. Proponents believe that the position of the planets influence conditions on earth, and that there’s a right and wrong time for nearly every human activity—including business activities. So naturally, that’s the philosophy that guides nearly all business decisions—from hiring to product launches—at the Chani app.\n\nChani is an astrology app and media company with just over 2 million downloads and an undisclosed number of paid subscribers. Last year, Inc. estimated the company’s annual revenue to be around $14 million. Founded by longtime astrological content creator Chani Nicholas and her wife, former Morgan Stanley associate Sonya Passi, the platform provides users with birth chart analysis as well as insight on dealing with certain astrological events, such as the infamous Saturn Return and the dreaded Mercury Retrograde.\n\nSabra Mohamed, Chani’s director of growth and marketer extraordinaire, wasn’t much of a believer in astrology before working at the company. But when she joined in 2022, she figured, well—as a marketer, you have to be able to sell anything, right?\n\nNow, after a few years working at Chani, Mohamed is a believer.\n\n“A lot of entrepreneurs will say, ‘It’s hard work, and I was lucky, I was there at the right time,’” Mohamed says. “We’re hacking that.”\n\n## What is electional astrology?\n\nAstrology focuses on the idea that the planets’ orbit in relation to each other can provide information about a person, place, or thing, and influence events or conditions on Earth.\n\nHere’s one way to think of it: If you check the weather, and you see one day it’s going to be sunny, you wear sunscreen and open a lemonade stand. If the weather forecast is thunderstorms and clouds, you might not launch your lemonade stand that day.\n\nExpand to continue reading ↓\n\n---\n\nTitle: CHANI: Your Astrology Guide — Review 2026: Sentiment & Intel\nURL: https://marlvel.ai/intel-re